	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Most such shields have a jarl's bindrune, whether or not they are carried by a dwarven jarl. Jarls are no longer a common part of dwarven society, but the practice of enchanting shields for the leaders of small warbands continues.</em></p><br><p>Attuning to this large shield item requires you to stand vigil to swear to become the leader or protector of a group of people, and requires you to have proficiency with medium armor.</p><br><p>Once per short rest, when attuned to this shield, you can use a bonus action to rally up to 6 friendly creatures within 30 ft. of you, who can then add [[/r 1d4]] to the first attack roll they make on their next turn.</p>",
